      "content": "We are given the curve \\(2x + x^2 y - y^3 = 2\\) and need to find the slope of the tangent line at the point \\((1,1)\\). To do this, we'll implicitly differentiate the equation with respect to \\(x\\) and then solve for \\(\\frac{dy}{dx}\\) at the point \\((1,1)\\)."
    },
